defaultDemocratic accountability is a fundamental condition.  The more we want to decentralise fiscal powers, the greater levels of direct representation we need to see.  We have made a case, for example, for a proportion of income tax to be assigned to combined authority areas.  If you are going to do that, you need a directly-elected mayor in order to give the visibility and accountability.  It is a little bit of horses-for-courses in this programme I am talking about.  If you want different levels of decentralisation, you need different types of democratic accountability.
