defaultCllr Box:default There has to be equalisation to make sure that those areas that are particularly deprived do not have a situation that is worsening.  That is my view.  You do also need incentives for those areas that are growing.  Those areas that perhaps do suffer deprivation now, once the equalisation has taken place, can move forward and try to engender the growth they actually want but in some areas is difficult, so I would agree with the comments that Ed and the previous panel made—particularly Tom, from the Leeds City Region perspective.
