defaultLiz Peacedefault: I do not have anything new to say, but I just say how much I agree with that point.  We should not lose sight of the fact that we are talking about allowing those people who are growing their business rate base to keep what they make.  If they are growing, we want them to keep it, so that, wherever and whoever they are, it is in their hands to encourage a greater degree of investment and development, and they then get the proceeds from that.
defaultOf course there are some that will need to be bailed out; there will always need to be a safety net for those who have not quite got into that positive process.  I do not see why those who have, who could be anywhere, should not be allowed to keep the proceeds of that growth.
